Add missing <stdlib.h> include for malloc/free in fmt's format.h.

fmt 11.1.3's include/fmt/format.h uses the unqualified C functions
`malloc` and `free` in detail::allocator (around line 747/752) but only
includes C++ headers such as <new> and <cstring>. On most standard
libraries those transitively pull in the C stdlib declarations, but
format.h defines _LIBCPP_REMOVE_TRANSITIVE_INCLUDES at the top of the
file, which makes libc++ strip exactly those transitive includes. Under
HEIR's hermetic clang + libc++ toolchain this leaves `malloc`/`free`
undeclared, breaking the build of fmt (and its consumers, e.g. SCIP/
SoPlex) with:

  error: use of undeclared identifier 'malloc'
  error: use of undeclared identifier 'free'

Upstream fmt fixed this on master by explicitly including <stdlib.h>
(// malloc, free); this patch backports that one-line include into the
existing #ifndef FMT_MODULE block. Drop once HEIR moves to an fmt
release that contains the upstream fix.

--- a/include/fmt/format.h
+++ b/include/fmt/format.h
@@ -41,6 +41,7 @@
 #include "base.h"

 #ifndef FMT_MODULE
+#  include <stdlib.h>  // malloc, free
 #  include <cmath>    // std::signbit
 #  include <cstddef>  // std::byte
 #  include <cstdint>  // uint32_t
